old aura versions

\skill{Skill cost 50xp ccf 1.5 "Proximity chock":} The character can choose to inflict damage on targets who move into base contact (not when the character moves into base contact).

\skill{Skill scf 1.0 ccf 1.3 "Damaging chockwave":} The character can inflict damage on everyone in base contact. Spend 1 mana or 1 stamina (decide when buying the skill), take one action, and roll for damaging chockwave. If successful the character inflicts 1 damage penetrating to everyone in base contact.

Heavier Damaging chockwave can be purchased for a multiple of the cost. E.g. 3dam chockwave can be bought for scf 3.0. Minor Damaging chockwave can be upgraded. Just re-calculate the spent XP and upgrade. Or multiple versions of Damaging chockwave can be bought separately.

Longer reaching chockwave, can be bought for a multiple the same way as heavier damaging aura.

E.g: a dam3 range2 aura has scf 6.0.






old feint text:

is a regular attack until the damage is rolled. If the character chooses to roll a d0 for the damage he has performed a feint. A feint pushes one less mod to the ams than the attack would otherwise do.
E.g. Feinting Fabio attacks with his rapier, but when the target blocks with his sword Fabio chooses to roll a d0 for damage, performing a feint. Since rapier is a fast+1 weapon, the attack would normally push mod-2 onto the ams, but when feinting it only pushes a mod-1. Very good to weaken out the opponent with lots of annoying attacks.




